---
import Section from "./Section.astro";
---

<Section
    class="border-t border-white/5 min-h-screen flex flex-col justify-center"
>
    <div class="w-full max-w-[1200px] mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mb-12">
            <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold">
                Most companies have data. <br />
                <span class="text-text-secondary"
                    >Few have decision systems.</span
                >
            </h2>
            <div
                class="text-lg text-text-secondary mt-8 space-y-4 max-w-3xl leading-relaxed"
            >
                <p>
                    Most organizations invest heavily in data infrastructure and
                    dashboards — especially Power BI.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Yet despite all that effort, teams still argue about
                    numbers, export data to Excel, or ignore dashboards
                    altogether.
                </p>
                <p>
                    What’s missing isn’t data or tooling. It’s the decision
                    layer: clear metrics, shared logic, and interfaces designed
                    around how people actually make decisions.
                </p>
                <p class="font-bold text-white mt-6">
                    This is where Power BI becomes powerful — not as a reporting
                    tool, but as a decision interface.
                    <span class="font-normal text-text-secondary"
                        >A place where logic, metrics, and design come together
                        to support real business decisions.</span
                    >
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
            <!-- Card 1: Static & Retrospective -->
            <div
                class="glass p-8 rounded-2xl card-hover transition-transform duration-300 ease-in-out"
            >
                <div class="mb-6 text-primary">
                    <svg
                        xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                        width="40"
                        height="40"
                        viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                        fill="none"
                        stroke="currentColor"
                        stroke-width="1.5"
                        stroke-linecap="round"
                        stroke-linejoin="round"
                        ><polyline points="23 6 13.5 15.5 8.5 10.5 1 18"
                        ></polyline><polyline points="17 6 23 6 23 12"
                        ></polyline></svg
                    >
                </div>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-3 text-white">
                    Static & Retrospective
                </h3>
                <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">
                    Dashboards show what happened last month — but not why it
                    happened or what to do next.
                </p>
                <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">
                    Metrics are descriptive, not actionable, leaving teams stuck
                    reacting instead of deciding.
                </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Card 2: Untrusted Metrics -->
            <div
                class="glass p-8 rounded-2xl card-hover transition-transform duration-300 ease-in-out"
            >
                <div class="mb-6 text-primary">
                    <svg
                        xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                        width="40"
                        height="40"
                        viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                        fill="none"
                        stroke="currentColor"
                        stroke-width="1.5"
                        stroke-linecap="round"
                        stroke-linejoin="round"
                        ><path
                            d="M10.29 3.86L1.82 18a2 2 0 0 0 1.71 3h16.94a2 2 0 0 0 1.71-3L13.71 3.86a2 2 0 0 0-3.42 0z"
                        ></path><line x1="12" y1="9" x2="12" y2="13"
                        ></line><line x1="12" y1="17" x2="12.01" y2="17"
                        ></line></svg
                    >
                </div>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-3 text-white">
                    Untrusted Metrics
                </h3>
                <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">
                    Different dashboards show different numbers for the same
                    KPI.
                </p>
                <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">
                    Without a shared semantic model, stakeholders lose trust —
                    and decision-making moves back to spreadsheets and meetings.
                </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Card 3: Ignored by the Business -->
            <div
                class="glass p-8 rounded-2xl card-hover transition-transform duration-300 ease-in-out"
            >
                <div class="mb-6 text-primary">
                    <svg
                        xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                        width="40"
                        height="40"
                        viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                        fill="none"
                        stroke="currentColor"
                        stroke-width="1.5"
                        stroke-linecap="round"
                        stroke-linejoin="round"
                        ><path d="M18.36 6.64a9 9 0 1 1-12.73 0"></path><line
                            x1="12"
                            y1="2"
                            x2="12"
                            y2="12"></line></svg
                    >
                </div>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-3 text-white">
                    Ignored by the Business
                </h3>
                <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">
                    Dashboards exist, but adoption is low.
                </p>
                <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm leading-relaxed">
                    Interfaces aren’t designed for real workflows, ownership is
                    unclear, and reports slowly drift out of relevance.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-12 text-center">
            <p class="text-xl text-text-secondary font-medium italic">
                The result: dashboards technically work — but decisions still
                happen elsewhere.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</Section>

<style>
    @media (hover: hover) {
        .card-hover:hover {
            transform: translateY(-0.25rem);
        }
    }
</style>
